        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Also `:help supported-platforms` does not help much if nvim does not start.\r\n\r\nBut Windows Server is missing all kinds of things (winver, explorer, vcrt, ...). Though I know it's common on remote cloud systems, and it would be good to have a better experience there.\r\n\r\n> neovim does not depend on vcruntime140.dll (static build? should be achievable with /MT flag)\r\n\r\nPerhaps we should consider that. But it makes the package much bigger for all users, which is unfortunate since the common case is that Windows has its standard tools available.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure it makes sense for a \"portable\" build to target a minimal system that is missing its standard tools. Instead, a package manager (scoop, winget) should be able to pull in what's needed for such a system.\r\n\r\n> neovim installer warns if vcruntime140.dll is missing\r\n\r\nThat's definitely where we should start. Is there any reference implementation for this? Does https://wixtoolset.org/ have a way to do it?",
